                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1518/191.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Root directs Mr. Rockhill, in expressing the felicitations of the President
                    and Government on the celebration of the accession to the Throne, to say that it
                    was particularly agreeable to the President to receive His Excellency T’ang
                    Shao-yi, His Imperial Majesty’s ambassador on the same auspicious day.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
